  "320:319": {
    "inputs": {
      "value": "Ultra-realistic cinematic dinosaur sequence. A powerful reddish-orange juvenile Tyrannosaurus-like dinosaur walks through a misty prehistoric forest at dawn. Highly detailed scales, subtle muscle movement beneath the skin, realistic breathing, blinking eyes, and natural weight shift in every step. Dense forest atmosphere with soft volumetric fog, floating dust particles, and warm golden sunlight rays piercing through tall trees. Small plants and flowers bend naturally as the dinosaur moves past them.\n\nThe dinosaur slowly emerges from the background and walks directly toward the camera with confident predatory behavior. Each footstep compresses the soil, creating subtle dust puffs and ground vibrations. Its tail swings naturally for balance while shoulder and neck muscles flex realistically. The dinosaur occasionally turns its head slightly left and right, scanning the environment like a hunter.\n\n**Camera movement:** Start with a low-angle cinematic tracking shot close to the ground, following alongside the dinosaur's front-left side. Smooth gimbal-style motion with slight handheld realism. The camera slowly dollies forward while orbiting around the dinosaur, maintaining shallow depth of field and strong subject focus. As the dinosaur advances, the camera lowers even further to emphasize scale and power. Mid-sequence, transition into a dramatic front-facing tracking shot moving backward as the dinosaur approaches, creating an intimidating sense of presence. Finish with a slow cinematic crane-up movement revealing the dinosaur dominating the forest environment.\n\nHalfway through the sequence, the dinosaur stops briefly, lifts its head upward, expands its chest, and releases a massive, terrifying roar. Its jaw opens wide, exposing sharp teeth and detailed mouth textures. Neck muscles tighten, throat vibrates, saliva strands stretch between the teeth, and the roar creates visible environmental reactions. Nearby leaves shake, dust lifts from the ground, and small birds burst from the trees in panic. The camera performs a subtle push-in during the roar to heighten intensity.\n\nAfter roaring, the dinosaur resumes walking forward with dominance and confidence. Sunlight glints across the textured scales while atmospheric fog drifts around its legs. Realistic motion blur, cinematic depth of field, dynamic lighting, physically accurate shadows, film-quality rendering, ultra-detailed textures, natural color grading, epic blockbuster wildlife documentary style, photorealistic animation, smooth camera transitions, stable movement, 4K HDR quality, high realism, realistic physics, professional VFX, immersive cinematic storytelling.\n\n**Negative prompt:** cartoon, low poly, toy appearance, plastic texture, unrealistic anatomy, extra limbs, distorted body, flickering, jitter, shaky camera, warped legs, floating feet, low resolution, blurry subject, oversaturated colors, unrealistic motion, frame artifacts, duplicated body parts, unnatural tail movement, poor lighting, CGI look, low-detail scales, motion glitches, deformed teeth, inconsistent shadows, unrealistic roar animation, fast jerky movement, camera stutter, text, watermark, logo.\n"
